{"title_page": "MaKami College", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n| name           = MaKami College\n| native_name    =\n| native_name_lang =\n| other_name     =\n| former_name    =\n| image          =\n| image_size     =\n| image_alt      =\n| caption        =\n| coordinates    = {{coord|53.5397|N|113.4232|W|display=inline}} (Edmonton location)\n| motto          = Hands on training and experience\n| motto_lang     =\n| mottoeng       =\n| established    = 2001\n| closed         =\n| type           = Massage Therapy College\n| parent         =\n| affiliation    =\n| endowment      =\n| budget         =\n| officer_in_charge =\n| chairman       =\n| chancellor     =\n| president      =\n| vice-president =\n| superintendent =\n| provost        =\n| vice_chancellor=\n| rector         =\n| principal      =\n| dean           =\n| director       =\n| head_label     =\n| head           =\n| academic_staff =\n| administrative_staff =\n| students       = 2000+\n| undergrad      =\n| postgrad       =\n| doctoral       =\n| other          =\n| city           = [[Edmonton]] & [[Calgary]]\n| state          =\n| province       = [[Alberta]]\n| country        = [[Canada]]\n| coor           =\n| campus         =\n| former_names   =\n| free_label     =\n| free           =\n| colors         =\n| colours        =\n| athletics      =\n| sports         =\n| nickname       =\n| mascot         =\n| affiliations   =\n| website        = https://www.makamicollege.com\n| logo           =\n| footnotes      =\n}}\n\n'''MaKami College''' is a provincially credited [[List of colleges in Alberta|private college in Alberta]] that trains students to become [[Massage therapists|licensed massage therapists]] and health care aides.  It was established in [[Edmonton]], [[Alberta]] in 2001 by the Pavkovic family and has expanded to large campuses in both Edmonton and [[Calgary]], Alberta.\n\n== History ==\n\nMaKami College started as a small [[vocational college]] in [[Edmonton]], AB and has since grown to an enrollment of over 2,000 students per year with a second campus opened in [[Calgary]] in 2013. In 2014 MaKami College was listed on Profit Guide's Profit 500 - Canada's Fastest Growing Companies list.<ref>{{cite web|title=2014 Profit 500|url=http://www.profitguide.com/microsite/profit500/2014|website=ProfitGuide.com|publisher=Profit Guide|accessdate=4 August 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140810153104/http://www.profitguide.com/microsite/profit500/2014|archive-date=10 August 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2019, MaKami College's Edmonton campus moved into the Boonie Doon shopping centre in the 10,219-square-metre space formerly occupied by the department store Sears.<ref>{{cite web|title=Massage therapy school MaKami College to set up in old Sears space in Bonnie Doon mall|url=https://edmontonjournal.com/business/local-business/massage-therapy-school-makami-college-to-set-up-in-old-sears-space-in-bonnie-doon-mall|website=EdmontonJournal.com|publisher=Edmonton Journal|accessdate=10 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Accreditation ==\n\nMaKami College is a member in good standing with NHP Canada, CRMTA, Canadian Sports Massage Therapists Association and the Better Business Bureau.<ref>{{cite web|title=Better Business Bureau|url=http://www.bbb.org/edmonton/business-reviews/massage-school/makami-college-of-massage-therapy-in-edmonton-ab-165243|publisher=Better Business Bureau|accessdate=27 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Edmonton Campus ==\n\nMaKami College's head office is located in a 110,000 sqft. space at the [[Bonnie Doon Shopping Centre]], at the intersection of [[Whyte Avenue]] and [[83 Street, Edmonton|83 Street]] in the [[Bonnie Doon, Edmonton|Bonnie Doon]] neighbourhood. It moved to this location in 2019 and houses all first and second-year massage therapy students as well as workshops for students and working RMTs.\n\nPrior to being located in the Bonnie Doon Shopping Centre, MaKami College's head office was located on the second floor of the former site of [[Capilano Mall (Edmonton)|Capilano Mall]], across from the [[Edmonton Public Library]]. When Capilano Mall, was heavily reconstructed in 2013,<ref>{{cite news|last=Maimann|first=Kevin|title=Stores in Capilano Mall in Edmonton Close the Doors|url=http://www.edmontonsun.com/2013/06/09/stores-in-capilano-mall-in-edmonton-close-the-doors|accessdate=27 August 2013|newspaper=The Edmonton Sun|date=June 9, 2013}}</ref> MaKami College remained in what remained of the previous building. Second-year students were relocated to a Sports Massage Facility Centre off 50 Street & 106 Ave.<ref>{{cite web|title=Makami Edmonton Campus Expands|url=http://makamicollege.com/news/2013/jun/14/makami-edmonton-campus-expands/|work=MaKami College|accessdate=27 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Calgary Campus ==\n\nOpened in 2013, the Calgary campus is located at 9618 Horton Rd SW, Calgary, AB. Enrollment in the Calgary massage therapy courses has been growing and the college has called their expansion a \"success\".<ref>{{cite web|title=MaKami Massage Therapy College Celebrates Success in Calgary|url=http://www.wireservice.ca/index.php?module=News&func=display&sid=11899|website=Wireservice.ca|publisher=Wire Service|accessdate=4 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn January 16, 2020 MaKami College announced that they've leased a 137,000 sq. ft. space in [[Marlborough Mall]].<ref>{{cite web |title=MaKami College Secures Space in Marlborough Mall |url=https://www.facebook.com/MaKamiCollege/photos/a.386479848056258/2649769801727240/?type=3&theater |website=Facebook |publisher=MaKami College |accessdate=February 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Community involvement ==\n\nSince 2001, MaKami College has been very involved in the community by sponsoring charity events and helping recent immigrants get skills and confidence to enhance job opportunities. MaKami College's managing director, Marija Pavkovic, is also the founder of the Queen Esther Education Foundation which helps recent immigrants with their ESL skills and assists with helping them find and secure employment opportunities. \"MaKami and Queen Esther were both my dreams, and to see them succeed and have people notice is such a great experience.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Edmonton Businesswoman Recognized in International Magazine|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/edmonton-businesswoman-recognized-international-magazine-133000177.html|accessdate=4 August 2014|work=Yahoo! Finance|agency=Red Queen Creative|publisher=Yahoo!|date=6 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and press ==\n\n* 2014 Profit 500 Fastest-Growing Companies in Canada, #62<ref>{{cite web|title=Canada's Fastest Growing Companies|url=http://www.profitguide.com/microsite/profit500/2014|website=Profit Guide|publisher=Profit Guide|accessdate=20 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140616011921/http://www.profitguide.com/microsite/profit500/2014/|archive-date=16 June 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* 2010 Edmonton Journal<ref>{{cite news|last1=Olsen|first1=Stephanie|title=More than a college, MaKami makes a difference in students' lives|url=http://www2.canada.com/edmontonjournal/news/story.html?id=a6c4ce2c-5dc2-4eca-8d84-6babb538cc1d|accessdate=4 August 2014|work=Edmonton Journal|publisher=Canada.com Network|date=14 February 2010}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Edmonton]]\n[[Category:Vocational education in Canada]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Calgary]]\n[[Category:Massage therapy]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox university\n| name           = MaKami College\n| native_name    =\n| native_name_lang =\n| other_name     =\n| former_name    =\n| image          =\n| image_size     =\n| image_alt      =\n| caption        =\n| coordinates    = {{coord|53.5397|N|113.4232|W|display=inline}} (Edmonton location)\n| motto          = Hands on training and experience\n| motto_lang     =\n| mottoeng       =\n| established    = 2001\n| closed         =\n| type           = Massage Therapy C